The paper discusses techniques for improving the performance of dynamic selection (DS) techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and pattern recognition. The paper focuses on prototype selection techniques, which are used to remove noise and redundant instances from the validation data. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data mining (cs.DM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Among these sub-categories, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely, as the paper deals with techniques for improving the performance of machine learning algorithms.
